elements.title: Mallard II
elements.contents: ... that the wooden-hulled Mallard II (pictured), built in 1936, is "probably the oldest operating dredge in California"?

elements.title: Hanne Nielsen
elements.contents: ... that Danish dairy farmer Hanne Nielsen created a Tilsit cheese for King Christian IX of Denmark?

elements.title: WBAW
elements.contents: ... that South Carolina radio station WBAW received a Peabody Award for public-service programming just six months after signing on the air?

elements.title: Jack G. Downing
elements.contents: ... that Jack G. Downing, the only person to serve as CIA station chief in Moscow and Beijing, "read Chinese poetry for kicks"?

elements.title: English Building
elements.contents: ... that according to campus legend, the English Building at the University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign is haunted by the ghost of a female student who drowned in the building's pool?

elements.title: Andreas Schnider
elements.contents: ... that Andreas Schnider, a theologian and local Austrian People's Party leader from Graz, holds a leading role in Austria's teacher training?

elements.title: Beddomeia waterhouseae
elements.contents: ... that the range of freshwater snail Beddomeia waterhouseae consists merely of a small tributary in Tasmania?

elements.title: prime minister of Zambia
elements.contents: ... that at the time the post was abolished, the prime minister of Zambia was being paid less than his secretary?
